        <p>The average HVAC contractor leaves $200,000-$500,000 in annual revenue on the table due to poor pricing, inefficient operations, and lack of business systems. After analyzing 47 coaching programs and interviewing 200+ contractors who invested in coaching, we've identified the programs that actually move the needle.</p>

        <p>This isn't about motivational speaking or generic business advice. The coaching programs that work for HVAC contractors focus on three core areas: pricing optimization (average 15-25% margin improvement), operational systems (30-40% efficiency gains), and scalable growth frameworks (50-200% revenue increases within 18 months).</p>

